line = 1659 | 1 | wire from Jonathan, saying that he leaves by the 6:25 to-night from
line = 1660 | 1 | Launceston and will be here at 10:18, so that I shall have no fear
line = 1661 | 1 | to-night. Will you, therefore, instead of lunching with us, please come
line = 1662 | 1 | to breakfast at eight o'clock, if this be not too early for you? You can
line = 1663 | 1 | get away, if you are in a hurry, by the 10:30 train, which will bring
line = 1664 | 1 | you to Paddington by 2:35. Do not answer this, as I shall take it that,
