line = 1938 | 1 | CHAPTER XV
line = 1939 | 1 | 
line = 1940 | 1 | DR. SEWARD'S DIARY--_continued_.
line = 1941 | 1 | 
line = 1942 | 1 | 
line = 1943 | 1 | For a while sheer anger mastered me; it was as if he had during her life
line = 1944 | 1 | struck Lucy on the face. I smote the table hard and rose up as I said to
line = 1945 | 1 | him:--
line = 1946 | 1 | 
line = 1947 | 1 | "Dr. Van Helsing, are you mad?" He raised his head and looked at me, and
line = 1948 | 1 | somehow the tenderness of his face calmed me at once. "Would I were!" he
line = 1949 | 1 | said. "Madness were easy to bear compared with truth like this. Oh, my
line = 1950 | 1 | friend, why, think you, did I go so far round, why take so long to tell
line = 1951 | 1 | you so simple a thing? Was it because I hate you and have hated you all
line = 1952 | 1 | my life? Was it because I wished to give you pain? Was it that I wanted,
line = 1953 | 1 | now so late, revenge for that time when you saved my life, and from a
line = 1954 | 1 | fearful death? Ah no!"
line = 1955 | 1 | 
line = 1956 | 1 | "Forgive me," said I. He went on:--
line = 1957 | 1 | 
line = 1958 | 1 | "My friend, it was because I wished to be gentle in the breaking to you,
line = 1959 | 1 | for I know you have loved that so sweet lady. But even yet I do not
line = 1960 | 1 | expect you to believe. It is so hard to accept at once any abstract
line = 1961 | 1 | truth, that we may doubt such to be possible when we have always
line = 1962 | 1 | believed the 'no' of it; it is more hard still to accept so sad a
line = 1963 | 1 | concrete truth, and of such a one as Miss Lucy. To-night I go to prove
line = 1964 | 1 | it. Dare you come with me?"
line = 1965 | 1 | 
line = 1966 | 1 | This staggered me. A man does not like to prove such a truth; Byron
line = 1967 | 1 | excepted from the category, jealousy.
line = 1968 | 1 | 
line = 1969 | 1 |     "And prove the very truth he most abhorred."
line = 1970 | 1 | 
line = 1971 | 1 | He saw my hesitation, and spoke:--
line = 1972 | 1 | 
line = 1973 | 1 | "The logic is simple, no madman's logic this time, jumping from tussock
line = 1974 | 1 | to tussock in a misty bog. If it be not true, then proof will be relief;
line = 1975 | 1 | at worst it will not harm. If it be true! Ah, there is the dread; yet
line = 1976 | 1 | very dread should help my cause, for in it is some need of belief. Come,
line = 1977 | 1 | I tell you what I propose: first, that we go off now and see that child
line = 1978 | 1 | in the hospital. Dr. Vincent, of the North Hospital, where the papers
line = 1979 | 1 | say the child is, is friend of mine, and I think of yours since you were
line = 1980 | 1 | in class at Amsterdam. He will let two scientists see his case, if he
line = 1981 | 1 | will not let two friends. We shall tell him nothing, but only that we
line = 1982 | 1 | wish to learn. And then----"
line = 1983 | 1 | 
line = 1984 | 1 | "And then?" He took a key from his pocket and held it up. "And then we
line = 1985 | 1 | spend the night, you and I, in the churchyard where Lucy lies. This is
line = 1986 | 1 | the key that lock the tomb. I had it from the coffin-man to give to
line = 1987 | 1 | Arthur." My heart sank within me, for I felt that there was some fearful
line = 1988 | 1 | ordeal before us. I could do nothing, however, so I plucked up what
line = 1989 | 1 | heart I could and said that we had better hasten, as the afternoon was
line = 1990 | 1 | passing....
line = 1991 | 1 | 
line = 1992 | 1 | We found the child awake. It had had a sleep and taken some food, and
line = 1993 | 1 | altogether was going on well. Dr. Vincent took the bandage from its
line = 1994 | 1 | throat, and showed us the punctures. There was no mistaking the
line = 1995 | 1 | similarity to those which had been on Lucy's throat. They were smaller,
line = 1996 | 1 | and the edges looked fresher; that was all. We asked Vincent to what he
line = 1997 | 1 | attributed them, and he replied that it must have been a bite of some
line = 1998 | 1 | animal, perhaps a rat; but, for his own part, he was inclined to think
line = 1999 | 1 | that it was one of the bats which are so numerous on the northern
line = 2000 | 1 | heights of London. "Out of so many harmless ones," he said, "there may
line = 2001 | 1 | be some wild specimen from the South of a more malignant species. Some
line = 2002 | 1 | sailor may have brought one home, and it managed to escape; or even from
line = 2003 | 1 | the Zoölogical Gardens a young one may have got loose, or one be bred
line = 2004 | 1 | there from a vampire. These things do occur, you know. Only ten days ago
line = 2005 | 1 | a wolf got out, and was, I believe, traced up in this direction. For a
line = 2006 | 1 | week after, the children were playing nothing but Red Riding Hood on the
line = 2007 | 1 | Heath and in every alley in the place until this 'bloofer lady' scare
line = 2008 | 1 | came along, since when it has been quite a gala-time with them. Even
line = 2009 | 1 | this poor little mite, when he woke up to-day, asked the nurse if he
line = 2010 | 1 | might go away. When she asked him why he wanted to go, he said he wanted
line = 2011 | 1 | to play with the 'bloofer lady.'"
line = 2012 | 1 | 
line = 2013 | 1 | "I hope," said Van Helsing, "that when you are sending the child home
line = 2014 | 1 | you will caution its parents to keep strict watch over it. These fancies
line = 2015 | 1 | to stray are most dangerous; and if the child were to remain out another
line = 2016 | 1 | night, it would probably be fatal. But in any case I suppose you will
line = 2017 | 1 | not let it away for some days?"
line = 2018 | 1 | 
line = 2019 | 1 | "Certainly not, not for a week at least; longer if the wound is not
line = 2020 | 1 | healed."
line = 2021 | 1 | 
line = 2022 | 1 | Our visit to the hospital took more time than we had reckoned on, and
line = 2023 | 1 | the sun had dipped before we came out. When Van Helsing saw how dark it
line = 2024 | 1 | was, he said:--
line = 2025 | 1 | 
line = 2026 | 1 | "There is no hurry. It is more late than I thought. Come, let us seek
line = 2027 | 1 | somewhere that we may eat, and then we shall go on our way."
line = 2028 | 1 | 
line = 2029 | 1 | We dined at "Jack Straw's Castle" along with a little crowd of
line = 2030 | 1 | bicyclists and others who were genially noisy. About ten o'clock we
line = 2031 | 1 | started from the inn. It was then very dark, and the scattered lamps
line = 2032 | 1 | made the darkness greater when we were once outside their individual
line = 2033 | 1 | radius. The Professor had evidently noted the road we were to go, for he
line = 2034 | 1 | went on unhesitatingly; but, as for me, I was in quite a mixup as to
line = 2035 | 1 | locality. As we went further, we met fewer and fewer people, till at
line = 2036 | 1 | last we were somewhat surprised when we met even the patrol of horse
line = 2037 | 1 | police going their usual suburban round. At last we reached the wall of
line = 2038 | 1 | the churchyard, which we climbed over. With some little difficulty--for
line = 2039 | 1 | it was very dark, and the whole place seemed so strange to us--we found
line = 2040 | 1 | the Westenra tomb. The Professor took the key, opened the creaky door,
line = 2041 | 1 | and standing back, politely, but quite unconsciously, motioned me to
line = 2042 | 1 | precede him. There was a delicious irony in the offer, in the
line = 2043 | 1 | courtliness of giving preference on such a ghastly occasion. My
line = 2044 | 1 | companion followed me quickly, and cautiously drew the door to, after
line = 2045 | 1 | carefully ascertaining that the lock was a falling, and not a spring,
line = 2046 | 1 | one. In the latter case we should have been in a bad plight. Then he
line = 2047 | 1 | fumbled in his bag, and taking out a matchbox and a piece of candle,
line = 2048 | 1 | proceeded to make a light. The tomb in the day-time, and when wreathed
line = 2049 | 1 | with fresh flowers, had looked grim and gruesome enough; but now, some
line = 2050 | 1 | days afterwards, when the flowers hung lank and dead, their whites
line = 2051 | 1 | turning to rust and their greens to browns; when the spider and the
line = 2052 | 1 | beetle had resumed their accustomed dominance; when time-discoloured
line = 2053 | 1 | stone, and dust-encrusted mortar, and rusty, dank iron, and tarnished
line = 2054 | 1 | brass, and clouded silver-plating gave back the feeble glimmer of a
line = 2055 | 1 | candle, the effect was more miserable and sordid than could have been
line = 2056 | 1 | imagined. It conveyed irresistibly the idea that life--animal life--was
line = 2057 | 1 | not the only thing which could pass away.
line = 2058 | 1 | 
line = 2059 | 1 | Van Helsing went about his work systematically. Holding his candle so
line = 2060 | 1 | that he could read the coffin plates, and so holding it that the sperm
line = 2061 | 1 | dropped in white patches which congealed as they touched the metal, he
line = 2062 | 1 | made assurance of Lucy's coffin. Another search in his bag, and he took
line = 2063 | 1 | out a turnscrew.
line = 2064 | 1 | 
line = 2065 | 1 | "What are you going to do?" I asked.
line = 2066 | 1 | 
line = 2067 | 1 | "To open the coffin. You shall yet be convinced." Straightway he began
line = 2068 | 1 | taking out the screws, and finally lifted off the lid, showing the
line = 2069 | 1 | casing of lead beneath. The sight was almost too much for me. It seemed
line = 2070 | 1 | to be as much an affront to the dead as it would have been to have
line = 2071 | 1 | stripped off her clothing in her sleep whilst living; I actually took
line = 2072 | 1 | hold of his hand to stop him. He only said: "You shall see," and again
line = 2073 | 1 | fumbling in his bag, took out a tiny fret-saw. Striking the turnscrew
line = 2074 | 1 | through the lead with a swift downward stab, which made me wince, he
line = 2075 | 1 | made a small hole, which was, however, big enough to admit the point of
line = 2076 | 1 | the saw. I had expected a rush of gas from the week-old corpse. We
line = 2077 | 1 | doctors, who have had to study our dangers, have to become accustomed to
line = 2078 | 1 | such things, and I drew back towards the door. But the Professor never
line = 2079 | 1 | stopped for a moment; he sawed down a couple of feet along one side of
line = 2080 | 1 | the lead coffin, and then across, and down the other side. Taking the
line = 2081 | 1 | edge of the loose flange, he bent it back towards the foot of the
line = 2082 | 1 | coffin, and holding up the candle into the aperture, motioned to me to
line = 2083 | 1 | look.
line = 2084 | 1 | 
line = 2085 | 1 | I drew near and looked. The coffin was empty.
line = 2086 | 1 | 
line = 2087 | 1 | It was certainly a surprise to me, and gave me a considerable shock, but
line = 2088 | 1 | Van Helsing was unmoved. He was now more sure than ever of his ground,
line = 2089 | 1 | and so emboldened to proceed in his task. "Are you satisfied now, friend
line = 2090 | 1 | John?" he asked.
line = 2091 | 1 | 
line = 2092 | 1 | I felt all the dogged argumentativeness of my nature awake within me as
line = 2093 | 1 | I answered him:--
line = 2094 | 1 | 
line = 2095 | 1 | "I am satisfied that Lucy's body is not in that coffin; but that only
line = 2096 | 1 | proves one thing."
line = 2097 | 1 | 
line = 2098 | 1 | "And what is that, friend John?"
line = 2099 | 1 | 
line = 2100 | 1 | "That it is not there."
line = 2101 | 1 | 
line = 2102 | 1 | "That is good logic," he said, "so far as it goes. But how do you--how
line = 2103 | 1 | can you--account for it not being there?"
line = 2104 | 1 | 
line = 2105 | 1 | "Perhaps a body-snatcher," I suggested. "Some of the undertaker's people
line = 2106 | 1 | may have stolen it." I felt that I was speaking folly, and yet it was
line = 2107 | 1 | the only real cause which I could suggest. The Professor sighed. "Ah
line = 2108 | 1 | well!" he said, "we must have more proof. Come with me."
line = 2109 | 1 | 
line = 2110 | 1 | He put on the coffin-lid again, gathered up all his things and placed
line = 2111 | 1 | them in the bag, blew out the light, and placed the candle also in the
line = 2112 | 1 | bag. We opened the door, and went out. Behind us he closed the door and
line = 2113 | 1 | locked it. He handed me the key, saying: "Will you keep it? You had
line = 2114 | 1 | better be assured." I laughed--it was not a very cheerful laugh, I am
line = 2115 | 1 | bound to say--as I motioned him to keep it. "A key is nothing," I said;
line = 2116 | 1 | "there may be duplicates; and anyhow it is not difficult to pick a lock
line = 2117 | 1 | of that kind." He said nothing, but put the key in his pocket. Then he
line = 2118 | 1 | told me to watch at one side of the churchyard whilst he would watch at
line = 2119 | 1 | the other. I took up my place behind a yew-tree, and I saw his dark
line = 2120 | 1 | figure move until the intervening headstones and trees hid it from my
line = 2121 | 1 | sight.
line = 2122 | 1 | 
line = 2123 | 1 | It was a lonely vigil. Just after I had taken my place I heard a distant
line = 2124 | 1 | clock strike twelve, and in time came one and two. I was chilled and
line = 2125 | 1 | unnerved, and angry with the Professor for taking me on such an errand
