line = 2472 | 1 | she been buried alive?" He groaned in anguish that not even hope could
line = 2473 | 1 | soften.
line = 2474 | 1 | 
line = 2475 | 1 | "I did not say she was alive, my child; I did not think it. I go no
line = 2476 | 1 | further than to say that she might be Un-Dead."
line = 2477 | 1 | 
line = 2478 | 1 | "Un-Dead! Not alive! What do you mean? Is this all a nightmare, or what
line = 2479 | 1 | is it?"
line = 2480 | 1 | 
line = 2481 | 1 | "There are mysteries which men can only guess at, which age by age they
line = 2482 | 1 | may solve only in part. Believe me, we are now on the verge of one. But
line = 2483 | 1 | I have not done. May I cut off the head of dead Miss Lucy?"
line = 2484 | 1 | 
